### ===========================================
### Book Library API Test File
### ===========================================
### Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code
### Click "Send Request" above each request
### ===========================================

### Get all books
GET http://localhost:3000/api/books

### Get all books with category filter (query parameter)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/books?category=fiction

### Get all books with category and minimum price filter
GET http://localhost:3000/api/books?category=fiction&minPrice=10

### Get single book (replace BOOK_ID with actual ID from previous responses)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/books/BOOK_ID

### Create a book
POST http://localhost:3000/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Great Gatsby",
  "author": "F. Scott Fitzgerald",
  "category": "fiction",
  "price": 12.99,
  "inStock": true
}

### Create another book
POST http://localhost:3000/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "1984",
  "author": "George Orwell",
  "category": "fiction",
  "price": 10.99,
  "inStock": true
}

### Create a non-fiction book
POST http://localhost:3000/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Sapiens",
  "author": "Yuval Noah Harari",
  "category": "non-fiction",
  "price": 15.99,
  "inStock": true
}

### Update book (replace BOOK_ID with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/books/BOOK_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 9.99
}

### Update book - change multiple fields
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/books/BOOK_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 11.99,
  "inStock": false
}

### Delete book (replace BOOK_ID with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/books/BOOK_ID

### Test 404 - Non-existent route
GET http://localhost:3000/api/nonexistent

### Test 404 - Non-existent book ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/books/000000000000000000000000
